{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"DE-RISKING PASS COMPLETE — experiments/spikes run, ambiguity resolved, child descriptions updated.\n\nLocked decisions (evidence in each child's \"De-risking results\" section + spike session log):\n1. `@AGENTS.md` import is PROVEN in Claude Code v2.1.211 (headless canary returned verbatim; official docs recommend the exact `@AGENTS.md` + `## Claude Code` pattern; max depth 4 hops; same-repo imports need no approval). No symlink fallback. → S0/eastbound-bald-raptors is resolved.\n2. Imports do NOT reduce context (\"load at launch\"). So the slimming comes from de-dup into docs; AGENTS.md itself must be lean. A COMPLETE lean AGENTS.md is ~152 lines (≤200 achievable) ONLY IF the Git/Gerrit section is condensed (~50 lines) and defers the full recipe to CONTRIBUTING.md; verbatim Gerrit → ~215-230 (misses). → S2 AC pinned to ≤200 + Gerrit-condense.\n3. S1 premise corrected: only the `idea` status is truly unhomed. Parent-first cascade is already authoritative in concurrency.md I4a (fold in only the gate-interaction nuance); linking/tags/session-log write-mechanics already in event-schema.md. New `docs/ticket-model.md` holds the agent-facing CONCEPT for idea+hierarchy+linking+tags with xrefs (no duplicated event bodies). Session-log type→event-schema.md; capture helper→user-guide.md.\n4. Rename breaks ZERO code — all src/ references are the CLAUDE_CODE_SESSION_ID env var or prose comments; no CI reference. Reference surface ~15 files. Also update the plan-review criteria text + the .codex fallback comment.\n5. S4 drift-guard must sync a DELIMITED region (the template is not byte-identical to a doc), not a whole file like the skills sync test.\n\nNo code changed; working tree clean; still on main. Next: run plan-review on the children, then dispatch as a Gerrit feature branch."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timesta